In Express, middleware is just a function with the signature `(req, res, next)`. Register it with `app.use()` before your routes so it runs on every request.

```js
const express = require('express');
const app = express();

// Logging middleware
app.use((req, res, next) => {
  console.log(`${req.method} ${req.path}`);
  next(); // pass control to the next handler
});

app.get('/', (req, res) => res.send('Hello'));

app.listen(3000);
```

Key points:

- **`next()` is required** — call it to hand

